        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>March 20th 1866</date>.</p>
            <p>Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I received in due time your<lb/> kind lines of ..., as also your
                issue<lb/> of this month, in which I had the<lb/> pleasure of perusing the
                article<lb/> concerning the laying of the cor<lb/>nerstone of the Temple
                “Emanu-el”<lb/> in <placeName>Curaçao</placeName>. The reason why<lb/> I did not ere
                this acknowledge<lb/> the receipt of the former &amp; express<lb/> my thanks for its
                amiable con<lb/>tents is merely on account of<lb/> the manifold business I was<lb/>
                overcharged with of late, but I<lb/> hope this delay will not pre<lb/>vent you from
                remaining con<lb/>vinced that the friendly feelings<lb/> therein manifested towards
                me<lb/> and fully reciprocated.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With regard to the insert<lb/>ion of the above mentioned<lb/>
                article, I must say that it<lb/> afforded me no little pleasure</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>as in my humble opinion you<lb/> have thereby given a signal<lb/> proof to the world,
                that while<lb/> advocating your principles<lb/> on the broad ground of Juda<lb/>ism
                you do not allow your<lb/> self to be made the champion<lb/> of any private party,
                which<lb/> while pretending to defend<lb/> religion do not aim but at<lb/>
                personalities. By the by let<lb/> me assure you that if you were<lb/> to become
                acquainted with<lb/> the two parties in <placeName>Curaçao</placeName> you<lb/> will
                soon find out that the<lb/> liberal one is by far not the<lb/> worst of the two.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Wishing to send my friends<lb/> there some copies of the said<lb/>
                number of the “Occident” you<lb/> will please remit me about<lb/> twenty five
                informing me at<lb/> the same time of their value.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Believe me Dear Sir, Yours Truly.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">A. J. Dovale</persName>.</p>
        </body>
